news.title: Blackstone in talks with Bain to sell $480 million stake in Embassy REIT: Sources
news.para: Embassy Office Parks was India's first REIT to list in 2019. It owns and operates more than 43.2 million square feet of office parks and office buildings in cities such as Bengaluru and Mumbai and is also the largest office REIT in Asia by area.

news.title: MIDC plot transfers to third party under GST scanner
news.para: The deals are being taken as lease which is classified as service and attracts GST. All such transfers since GST came into effect in 2017 are being now covered for the tax demand.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's sales bookings rise 12% to Rs 396 crore
news.para: "We had pre-sales of around Rs 396 crore in Q3 FY23, up 12 per cent on YoY (Year on Year) basis," the Mumbai-based firm said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Haryana Sehri Vikas Pradhikaran to audit institutional areas to check status of plots
news.para: According to the Haryana Sehri Vikas Pradhikaran policy, the owner of the property needs to apply with the HSVP and submit a fee if they want to lease out a portion of their property.

news.title: Gurugram: Company operating Basai plant ready to pick demolition waste, MCG yet to take call
news.para: With the increase in unauthorised dumping of C&D waste across the city, MCG is mulling over to hire a private agency for collecting the waste and is likely to consider the company’s proposal.

news.title: Coastal regulation zone clearance recommended for metro construction in Chennai
news.para: CMRL said the tunnels between Greenways Road Station and Adyar Junction station require an emergency evacuation shaft at the bank of Adyar as the two stations are 1200m apart.

news.title: Haryana government pays Rs 1.5 crore property tax to Chandigarh civic body
news.para: Sources said Rs 1.42 crore tax is of the Haryana mini-secretariat building in Sector 17 and the remaining Rs 9 crore of its allied building.

news.title: Pune civic body proposes town planning scheme in Wadgaonsheri on 47 acres of land
news.para: Once approved, this will be the third town planning scheme in the PMC area and the first in Wadgaonsheri. Around 47 acres of land will be utilised in the area for this purpose.

news.title: Indore: 1300 villagers identified for government patta scheme
news.para: Indore collector Ilayaraja T on Monday held a time-limit meeting and reviewed progress of different schemes and programmes of the government.

news.title: Dust screens missing at most construction sites in Nashik
news.para: The NMC, in January 2020, had come up with this rule in order to curb air pollution. Initially, all the construction sites used the dust screens, but with time a section of the builders started to give the nets a miss.

news.title: Gujarat HC upholds order allowing redevelopment of society in Vejalpur
news.para: The case involved Swami Vivekanandnagar Cooperative Housing Society where out of 78 flat owners, 74 (93%) consented to redevelopment citing dilapidated condition of buildings which were constructed in 1969.

news.title: Buildings on green belt to trigger snarls, stop auction of plots: RWA to Haryana CM
news.para: In the letter, members of Qutab Plaza Enclave RWA said buildings, once allowed in the area, would impede traffic and lead to jams, apart from violating laws related to green spaces.

news.title: Banks transfer Jaypee Infratech's Rs 9,234-crore debt to NARCL
news.para: IDBI Bank CEO Rakesh Sharma confirmed the transfer without naming the account. IDBI Bank is the lead lender in the account with dues of ₹3,750 crore. Sharma said the transfer to NARCL will reduce the bank's gross non-performing assets by 2.2 percentage points.

news.title: India Cements signs new wage agreement with trade unions
news.para: The four-year agreement effective from April 1, 2022 provides for a total increase of Rs 5,000 per month for the workmen employed in all the 10 cement plants of the company. The agreement will benefit over 500 workmen.

news.title: Amazon Development Center leases two lakh sq ft office space in Pune's Kharadi
news.para: The company has picked up the office space spread over four floors for a tenure of 10 years with total rentals of over Rs 208 crore, including rental escalations.
